stylometry:
Optimization is altering decision varaibles in order to minimize or maximize an outcome. An example of this is profit maximizing. For example, If I own a manufacturing plant that makes different pieces of clothing I can use an optimization model to figure out which pieces to make and how many of each in order to obtain the greatest profit. This can also work in minimizing. An optimatization model can also be used to figure out how to minimize cost. For example, by comparing how much it costs to make each piece of clothing in comparison to how much profit can be made off of each piece, a model can be constructed which demonstrates how to meet demand while minimizing cost.
Components of Linear Programming:
Decision Variables:(changing cells) the variables that can be altered in order to achieve the 	          objective.
Target Cell: the cell that obtains the objective function which is the goal that is trying to be achieved in the problem.
Constraints: the limitations and conditions that must be satified in order for the objective to be met.
